Subject: [PATCH 03/14] Fix non-functional init_opts parameter, bug #422471
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

If INIT_OPTS='' is not specified before the argument loop, scoping rules
will prevent it from being seen by the switch_root invocation.

Signed-off-by: Toralf FÃ¶rster <toralf.foerster@gmx.de>
Signed-off-by: Richard Yao <ryao@gentoo.org>
---
 defaults/linuxrc | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/defaults/linuxrc b/defaults/linuxrc
index 4166396..f1e20ce 100755
--- a/defaults/linuxrc
+++ b/defaults/linuxrc
@@ -38,6 +38,7 @@ CMDLINE=$(cat /proc/cmdline)
 FAKE_ROOT=''
 FAKE_INIT=''
 REAL_ROOTFLAGS=''
+INIT_OPTS=''
 ROOTFSTYPE='auto'
 CRYPT_SILENT=0
 
